[?2004l[?2004h> BUG FIX SUMMARY
[?2004l[?2004h> ===============
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> Problem:
[?2004l[?2004h> --------
[?2004l[?2004h> The scheduler was sending meeting reminders at incorrect times (off by 1 hour)
[?2004l[?2004h> for meetings between 2am-3am local time, specifically during DST transitions.
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> Root Cause:
[?2004l[?2004h> -----------
[?2004l[?2004h> In app.py, the convert_to_berlin() function was using:
[?2004l[?2004h>   berlin_dt = BERLIN_TZ.localize(utc_dt)
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> This incorrectly treated the naive datetime (which represented UTC) as if it
[?2004l[?2004h> were already in Berlin time, then just added timezone info.
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> The Fix:
[?2004l[?2004h> --------
[?2004l[?2004h> Changed to the correct two-step conversion:
[?2004l[?2004h>   utc_dt_aware = UTC_TZ.localize(utc_dt)      # Mark as UTC
[?2004l[?2004h>   berlin_dt = utc_dt_aware.astimezone(BERLIN_TZ)  # Convert to Berlin
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> This properly handles DST transitions.
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> Example (Maintenance Window Prep meeting):
[?2004l[?2004h> ------------------------------------------
[?2004l[?2004h> UTC Time: 2024-03-31 01:30:00
